I miss all my friends who are on the beach trip right now. Come back to me!!!

I just finished cleaning up my room. heh... it is still not clean though, there is always something else that needs to be done. I spent the night with meaghan last night, poor thing, I think she got food poisoning or something cuz she was throwing up all night. After I took a shower at her house me and laura went out to lunch... fun stuff.

I start my job saturday. I still have to go buy some scrubs from walmart or something. That is going to be a LONG day (7-4). Hopefully it will be fun.
Plenty of hot guys work there though, so I should be okay... just kidding (i think).

Just got back from the tanning bed... so I am all relaxed

I just spent the last hour cleaning up my room. It needed it pretty bad since we got rid of our cleaning lady (and because I am lazy).

Honor's day wasn't that bad, probably because it was my grade being announced this year. Of course it sucked because they didn't announce my scholorship... eh, nobody cares about me. :(

Tonight was the best I have had in a long time...

Adam's drum solo ROCKED! everybody loved it
Me and Laura had a lot of fun up there. Messed up a little, but no biggie. Got to practice before we do it again sunday though.
Meg and Jack were so cute when they did their duet, it was b-e-a-utiful...
Jacks monologue was so sad... i don't know what I am going to do without her next year.
KT's poetry was good mind you... but it still cracked me up, I love that girl 
Laura and Ash's video was great, especially our old JH pictures.
And finally Mae and Pat were just so talented they didn't even have to do anything other than sit there! 
And for the question of the day- Where was John Sherer? I am going to have to get on to him. His speech would've been good.

Hehe me jackie and mae cellophane wrapped Patrick's car. It was COMPLETELY covered. Jack and Magen wanted to get him back for something and I just wanted to get in on the action. It was great, eventually i'll post a picture of it.

Me and my mom have somehow managed fight ALL DAY LONG... even when Lindz got home, they fought too. I don't know what is wrong with her.

Well I have a busy day tomorrow. I am getting my hair cut at 10:00, then off to my second interview at caldwell mill animal clinic (i think i am going to get it!) then off to honors day. sigh... I hate busy days

Well... now that its summer I finally feel like writing in here again...go figure right? I just took a shower and I have to go dry my hair cuz tonight me and laura are doing sign language to this awesome song for the rest of our youth group... its gonna be lots of fun. Especially since we are also going to be doing it for graduation sunday. whew... that is going to be a busy day for me. 

I am considering just not going to the baccalaureate at all. It would make my day a lot easier. Anybody else with me? hehe, probably not.

Well... sittin here eating a chick-fil-a biscuits. yummy.
I am bored out of my mind cuz my entire youth group is gone to Alaska for World Changers (which for the 3rd year in a row I have missed because of cheerleading camp...blah) But I feel a lot better cuz tonight im a gonna go hang out with ma gurlz! I just got back from an eye appointment and guess what! I DON'T have to get glasses cuz I am only slightly near sighted in my left eye... whew... I would hate to have to bother with contacts. But he said that it would most likely get worse so in about a year I should come back and I will most likely have to get glasses... o well. I also had have an appointment with the orthopedic doctor this afternoon... yeah yeah I'm a hypochondriac.

I had a lot of fun last night cuz I was at the Tim McGraw concert! It was a lot of fun...lol I called carlyn in the middle of it and let her listen to a song. I saw warren, sarah, charles, caroline R, caroline T, and the Prichard family lol. I got a t-shirt so be warned that I might wear it a LOT.

Just got back from a day spent shopping with my mom. We went to gap and found me some shorts (since I was in dire need of some). Meg let me borrow Last Samurai and I watched it last night... it was one of the few movies that made me cry lol. Well... I have nothing else to say, basically updating so people don't get too mad at me. ttyl

Just got back from church after spending a long day running wires throughout the building. I saw Brandon there but I couldn't fing Drew. For lunch Scott Holt, Chris Harris, and I went out to eat Pizza Hut... it was fun. I will also be there tomorrow morning if anyone wants to come visit me. 

Tomorrow, my family and I are going to the lake with the Holts and we are going to watch ALL THREE of the LOTR's! It is going to be awesome!

Now that summer is here, I think I feel more up to writing. I'm very much dreading getting my exam scores back cuz I have a bad feeling about English and History. Well... Saturday I woke up at 7:00 and went mountain bike riding. I did the entire trail which is 16 miles. I think it was one of the hardest things I had ever done, but I felt good afterwards. Later I went to Erin's house and we had a lot of fun... to sum it up, segway, vegetable rice, master and commander, mnm's, pillow fight... it was great fun. Sunday the youth choir was singing in the early service so I went early to listen to them. Then we went to a mexican restraunt after sunday school. Laura came over that afternoon to see what Greer's newly painted room looked like. Then I helped her study for her chemistry exam. After that we had a lot of fun eating the different flavors of jellybeans, haha... we even turned it into a game... we are such dorks. 

Way back in January I submitted an essay for a scholarship called "Juniors what's your story." They posted the winners on the internet today and I was really hoping I would get it but I didn't... I was really disappointed cuz it was 9 $25,000 scholarships per state. o well
I had a dentist appointment today... I have to go back cuz they are going to redo 2 fillings and add another one...ouch. 

On a brighter note... LORD OF THE RINGS COMES OUT ON DVD TOMORROW! I haven't seen it yet but I heard it was the best one!

Brandon, Kevin, and I are in the library doing "latin." But we eventually just gave up and decided to play with out livejournals. I have to go to the physical and the civic center after school today. I hate those. But I'll be fine cuz I am going to Erin's house after I go buy her a present (*sigh* she is such a hassle) Well... I guess I better go cuz Sam is gonna get mad at me for not doing Latin. Buh Bye

So a lot has happened the past week.

Friday I went right after school to get my hair done cuz I had prom that night. That was the first time I have ever actually liked my hair after I got it done. Then I went and picked up Adam's boutineer. After that I went to Meaghan's house cuz we were all going to meet there and get ready. So I got ready with Meaghan and Magen until everybody arrived. Some of Meg's older sisters friends came to the house to. So all in all, there were about 10 girls there, plus their dates, plus their mothers, it was pretty crowded. So when we finished taking the usual pictures, we set out to Kobe's. We had reservations for 7:00 but when we got there at 6:30, they seated us right away. Well... a lot of people were at that same restraunt that night. Amy's surpise bday party was there, so I got to see all of them which was awesome. Also Carlyn's pathetic ex-boyfriend was there too. After we finished eating we went to the dance which was at the Harbert Center in downtown birmingham. We were one of the first to get there which was kind of pathetic, but at least we didn't have to wait to get out pictures taken. So we danced for about 3 hours straight... it was awesome. After the dance we went back to Meaghan's house and watched a movie. The guys left at about 2:30ish and we went straight to sleep. 

The next morning we woke up and Meaghan fixed up breakfast. We couldn't think of anything to do to pass the time, so we just all came over to my house and watched Gothika, which was a lot of fun. Then we left straight from my house to go meet some other people at Richard's bbq, but it was a disappointment because the train was not running that day sigh... Then we all piled up in a few cars and drove over to Vestavia to see the play, "Anything Goes." Jackie did awesome and it was one of the best plays I have ever seen, with plenty of crossdressers and gay people in it...haha. ahem, anyways, I saw a lot of people there, including Kevin and Alex. So after that I went back to Laura's house and we fell asleep to the movie High Crimes.

Sunday I went to church and we had a great lesson on the Second Coming in sunday school. I didn't feel like going home after church so me and Laura went and got Wendy's and then went to her house to finish watching School of Rock. I went home after that and pretty much just watched TV. My parents came home from the beach that night and Lindsey came home from visiting Grant at Vanderbuilt. 

Monday I stayed home from school cuz I felt like I was going to throw up the whole day. I still felt that way the next day but went to school anyways cuz I didn't want my makeup work to get to be too much. We didn't have school today cuz our superintendent's son died. So Carlyn, Amy, Grey, and I all went to Vestavia to eat lunch with them. We had to tell them we were from the Bwood student stampede thought, otherwise they wouldn't let us in. Well... Im going to leave for church in a little while. Carlyn, Amy, Morgan, Warren, and I'm not sure who else are going to the Puddle of Mud concert tonight. They asked me if I wanted to go, but since I only know like 2 of their songs I decided to go to church instead. 
 
Well... I hope that brings everybody up to date, cuz my hands are tired.

Well... I've been overcome by some very strange feeling and I actually wanted to write in my journal! strange huh?

I turned in my english critical paper this morning, and I hope that it was the last paper I will have to write this year (fingers crossed). We had this boring fine arts assembly this morning... I hate sports recognitions! blah... but I think that was the last one. So only one month left of school... it seems to be slowly winding down. 

I have the Spain Park prom this friday... I'm really stressed out cuz I have to make time for a hair and makeup appointment after school and get back to Meaghan's house by 5:45. But regardless, I can't wait till Friday comes! It should be a lot more fun than the B'wood dances because then I can actually booty dance (or whatever I want to do). Nope, you can't do that at our dances because all the teachers basically make a circle around you and watch you dance. Plus, Meaghan is going to be there and dance with me! We are either going to Kobe's or Stix... not sure, but either one is bound to be a disaster because all the people I know who make reservations there don't get seated for a while. But maybe this time it will be different. We are having the after-dance party at Meaghan's house. Laura will come over later and spend the night with me, Meaghan, and Magen. I CAN'T WAIT!

My dad bought four new movies Sunday and I have suceeded in watching all of them. I watched Gothika, Something's Gotta Give, Cheaper by the Dozen, and Beyond Borders. And yet I still crave more movies, guess I am just a movie freak. WOW... did anybody watch One Tree Hill tonight? That was some drama...

Went to look for a Prom dress saturday with Laura.... we went all the way to Cullman and I still didn't find anything (unless i want to rent the one I really like for $300... I don't think so). So I was sort of in a bad mood Saturday or maybe I was just tired cuz I went mountain bike riding and rode 11 miles. I practically slept the rest of the day. During cheerleading practice we looked through a magazine a different uniform styles, cuz this year is the year we can order new ones. I can't wait to see what we get. After practice I went to Erin's house to watch the edited version of out English project. I have to say she did a great job (although she put a little too many embarrassing thing about me in there). If your in my English class you'll get to see it!
